#: ../../source/cloud/history.rst:2
msgid "云发展史"
msgstr "Cloud Development History"

#: ../../source/cloud/history.rst:4
msgid ""
"在2000年到2010年间，云计算主要在 IaaS 的方向发展。 "
"在这个阶段以前，硬件、机房独立维护，运维成本高。应用部署、迁移困难，隔离性差。因此出现了 IaaS "
"，以基础设施做为服务，通过规模化部署来降低边际成本。 IaaS 的核心是各种虚拟化技术。 在这个时间段，出现了许多相关的虚拟化工具、商业化产品。"
msgstr ""
"From 2000 to 2010, cloud computing mainly developed in the "
"direction of IaaS. Before this stage, hardware and server rooms were "
"maintained independently, operations and maintenance costs were high, "
"application deployment and migration were difficult, and isolation was poor. "
"IaaS therefore emerged, providing infrastructure as a service and reducing "
"marginal costs through deployment at scale. The core of IaaS is a variety of "
"virtualization technologies. During this period, many related virtualization "
"tools and commercial products appeared."

#: ../../source/cloud/history.rst:9
msgid ""
"2000年，FreeBSD Jail 实现了第一个功能完整的操作系统虚拟化技术。 2001年，VMWare 发布 ESX 和 GSX "
"，推出虚拟化技术。同年，基于动态二进制翻译的 QEMU 发布。 2002年，亚马逊上线了Amazon Web Services。 "
"2005年，Intel 推出了 VT-x 硬件辅助虚拟化技术。 2006年，KVM 诞生。同年，亚马逊发布了EC2 (Elastic "
"Compute Cloud) 和 S3 (Simple Storage Service) 产品。 2008年，谷歌发布了第一版Google App"
" Engine。 2010年，微软发布了Microsoft Azure。 2010年，开源软件 OpenStack "
"发布并成立社区。OpenStack 本质上是一组分配、管理虚拟机的自动化工具脚本。在 OpenStack 发布以后，许多做 IaaS "
"的厂商都使用了 OpenStack 。"
msgstr ""
"In 2000, FreeBSD Jail implemented the first fully functional operating "
"system virtualization technology. In 2001, VMWare released ESX and GSX, "
"bringing virtualization technology to market. In the same year, QEMU, based "
"on dynamic binary translation, was released. In 2002, Amazon launched Amazon "
"Web Services. In 2005, Intel introduced VT-x hardware-assisted virtualization"
" technology. In 2006, KVM was created. In the same year, Amazon released EC2 "
"(Elastic Compute Cloud) and S3 (Simple Storage Service). In 2008, Google "
"released the first version of Google App Engine. In 2010, Microsoft released "
"Microsoft Azure. In 2010, the open source software OpenStack was released and"
" its community was established. OpenStack is essentially a set of automation "
"tool scripts for allocating and managing virtual machines. After OpenStack "
"was released, many IaaS vendors adopted it."

#: ../../source/cloud/history.rst:18
msgid ""
"IaaS 平台一定程度上提高了物理资源的利用效率，但是虚拟机在资源利用上仍然存在局限性。随后2011年到2013年期间，PaaS "
"开始逐渐成型，用于支持应用程序的完整生命周期，提供应用托管的能力。"
msgstr ""
"IaaS platforms improved physical resource utilization to a certain extent, "
"but virtual machines still had limitations in resource efficiency. "
"Subsequently, from 2011 to 2013, PaaS gradually took shape to support the "
"complete application lifecycle and provide application hosting capabilities."

#: ../../source/cloud/history.rst:20
msgid ""
"2011年，由 VMWare 开发的 CloudFoundry 做为第一款 PaaS "
"平台开源。支持应用打包、部署、以容器的方式运行、负载均衡等功能。 2011年11月，Google Compute Engine发布。 "
"2012年，OpenShift 开源。 2013年，Docker开源并发布，通过镜像的方式解决了应用开发、测试、生成环境不一致的问题。"
msgstr ""
"In 2011, CloudFoundry, developed by VMWare, was open sourced as the first "
"PaaS platform. It supported application packaging, deployment, containerized "
"execution, load balancing, and other functions. In November 2011, Google "
"Compute Engine was released. In 2012, OpenShift was open sourced. In 2013, "
"Docker was open sourced and released, using images to solve inconsistencies "
"between application development, testing, and production environments."

#: ../../source/cloud/history.rst:25
msgid ""
"2013年以后，云计算越来越成熟。规模也越来越大，容器的规模部署与管理成为了问题。Docker 发布了 Swarm ，而 Google 则发布了 "
"Kubernetes 。"
msgstr ""
"After 2013, cloud computing became increasingly mature and continued to grow "
"in scale. Large-scale container deployment and management became a problem. "
"Docker released Swarm, while Google released Kubernetes."

#: ../../source/cloud/history.rst:27
msgid ""
"2013年，云原生概念被提出。 2014年，Google 发布 Kubernetes。 "
"2015年，Google宣布成立CNCF基金会（云原生计算）。"
msgstr ""
"In 2013, the concept of cloud native was proposed. In 2014, Google released "
"Kubernetes. In 2015, Google announced the establishment of the CNCF "
"foundation (Cloud Native Computing Foundation)."
